mm/userfaultfd: detect VMA replacement after copy retry in mfill_copy_folio_retry()

This patch takes a snapshot of a VMA's inode and flags before dropping locks
to retry copy_from_user(). It then compares the snapshot after re-acquiring
the locks to detect if the VMA was replaced.

> diff --git a/mm/userfaultfd.c b/mm/userfaultfd.c
> index 481ec7eb4442..22e82f953eb5 100644
> --- a/mm/userfaultfd.c
> +++ b/mm/userfaultfd.c

[ ... ]

> +static void vma_snapshot_take(struct vm_area_struct *vma,
> +			      struct vma_snapshot *s)
> +{
> +	s->flags = vma->vm_flags;
> +	if (vma->vm_file) {
> +		s->inode = vma->vm_file->f_inode;
> +		ihold(s->inode);

Does using ihold() without pinning the vfsmount allow the superblock to be
freed?

If userspace closes the file and unmounts the filesystem while the lock is
dropped in mfill_copy_folio_retry(), the unmount can succeed because there
are no active vfsmount references.

When iput() is called later, iput_final() could dereference inode->i_sb->s_op
on a freed superblock and cause a use-after-free.

> +	} else {
> +		s->inode = NULL;
> +	}
> +}
