Does using ihold() without pinning the vfsmount allow the superblock to be
freed?

If userspace closes the file and unmounts the filesystem while the lock is
dropped in mfill_copy_folio_retry(), the unmount can succeed because there
are no active vfsmount references.

When iput() is called later, iput_final() could dereference inode->i_sb->s_op
on a freed superblock and cause a use-after-free.

