Can this dereference a NULL pointer if an anonymous VMA replaces a
file-backed VMA?

If the original VMA was file-backed, s->inode is non-NULL. If the replacing
VMA is anonymous but shares the exact same vm_flags, the previous flags
check passes, but vma->vm_file will be NULL, causing a crash when accessing
f_inode.

