Does calling iput() through vma_snapshot_release() while holding the
mmap_lock or per-VMA lock create an ABBA deadlock hazard?

The locks are reacquired by mfill_get_vma() just before this out label.
If this iput() drops the final reference to the inode, it triggers
evict_inode() which can acquire core filesystem locks like i_rwsem.

The standard kernel lock ordering is i_rwsem before mmap_lock. Acquiring
i_rwsem while holding mmap_lock inverts this order.

